It causes an increase in blood volume within arteries, potentially lowering cardiac reserve volume (CRV). This situation may lead the body to compensate by increasing its pump capacity or reducing tissue resistance through mechanisms like endogenous counterpressures, ultimately contributing to higher blood pressure if these compensations are insufficient.
